2 unit(s) Beyond Meat®
6 unit(s) Flour Tortillas
85 g Tortilla Chips
1 unit(s) Sour Cream
113 g Corn Kernels
1 tbsp Mexican Seasoning
1 cup Cheddar Cheese, shredded
3 tbsp Guacamole
1 tbsp Tex-Mex Paste
1.5 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat.
When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then Beyond Meat® patties, Tex-Mex paste, Mexican Seasoning and corn.
Cook, breaking up patties into smaller pieces, until crispy, 5-6 min.**
Season with salt and pepper.

On a clean surface, arrange tortillas.
Add Beyond Meat® mixture on one side of each tortilla. Top with tortilla chips (about 3-4 chips per tortilla), then sprinkle cheese over top.
Fold each tortilla over onto itself and firmly press to close.
Arrange quesadillas on a foil-lined baking sheet.

Brush quesadillas with 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil.
Broil in the middle of the oven, flipping halfway through cooking, until golden-brown and cheese has melted, 2-3 min per side.

Stir together sour cream and guacamole in a small bowl.
Divide Beyond Meat® crunch quesadillas between plates.
Serve remaining tortilla chips and creamy guacamole on the side for dipping.

If you've opted to get Beyond Meat®, cook it the same way as the turkey, breaking up patties into smaller pieces, until crispy, 5-6 min.**